- A closure is a function that has access to variables in its lexical scope, even after the scope has closed. Example:

      ```dart
      Function makeAdder(int addBy) {
        return (int i) => addBy + i;
      }

      var add2 = makeAdder(2);
      print(add2(3)); // 5
      ```

